52 Bard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ubrinklith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brinklith</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/00 5:56:20 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/legendward/brink.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: no weapons!</span><hr size=1> That's what I thought Quemn, but you'd be surprised at how many bards seem to think the best way they contribute to a group is by being a third rate tank... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><b>Brinklith Rioghbhardan</b> - Jester of Avalon<br>
<a href="http://www.geocities.com/mastersofavalon" target="_blank">Masters of Avalon</a><br>
Bard of Bristlebane<br>
<a href="http://www.brellserilis.net" target="_blank">Brell Serilis Server</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uatwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AtWork</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/00 8:37:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bard Question #1 - Dragons</span><hr size=1> Well, I've been on a few raids and the strangest thing has happened.  Most of the time I was stuck with a nuke group.  I did not speak up the first few times, being a raid newbie, but I finally had to say no.  Like, how is mana regen going to really help when you are trying to take something down fast?  After I got placed a tank group, it was great.  Got out my drum and banged on Elemental and Guardian.  Thought about Niv's, but the lag has always been bad for me; even with stuff turned off.  So I concentrated on those two songs only.  The tank group stayed up the whole fight with no losses.  Resisted fears and most of the breath damage too.<br>
<br>
Resists, in a tank group, is our best use...imho.<br>
<br>
Tatter D'Malion<br>
Bardette <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uquemnwyndrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quemn Wyndrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/00 4:19:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bard Question #1 - Dragons</span><hr size=1> a bard should always be in a tank group...unless there are already ones in all of them (like theres that many of us). they should be right under the dragon next to the tanks singing with drum, no question about it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ubrinklith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brinklith</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/7/00 5:49:47 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/legendward/brink.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bard Question #1 - Dragons</span><hr size=1> /agree Quemn<br>
