Bard of Bristlebane<br>
<a href="http://www.brellserilis.net" target="_blank">Brell Serilis Server</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ukalsyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalsyre</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/17/00 6:24:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bard Question #1 - Dragons</span><hr size=1> I have been on a dragon raid or two, so I will comment on what I know.<br>
<br>
Bards are more of a luxury when it comes to Dragons.  You dont need them to win, but its awfully nice to have a few around.  Bards are best at a dragon raid when they sing their resist songs.  Even a level 40 Bard with a MM drum can be of benefit to a Vox or Nag raid by adding 40ish points of resist to Magic/Cold/Fire with just one song to a party of 6.<br>
<br>
However, many raid goers can reach a very high level of resists by using specific gear, potions, and spells.  This means the Bard song is now not as important.  If your tanks all have resists near 255 without the song, why add more resists?<br>
<br>
I still do sing resist songs at Dragon raids.  With a selos drum at level 55 I think my Elemental does about 78 points of resist for Magic/Cold/Fire.  I have also found Cantana to be of benefit since it eliminates all fatigue problems as well as regen mana and health.  Since it is &quot;Twistable&quot; I find it beneficial to both the tanks and clerics in my Dragon raid group.<br>
<br>
Now there have been a few raids I was on where I did switch from drum to sword.  Like when all the Tanks are dead and its the Bard and 2 OOM clerics.  Another time I got to swing is the draco-liche.  I went with VoV and Pslam of Mystic shielding.  A final example is when you are just dominating a dragon so easily you switch and swing just for fun.<br>
<br>
But, for the most part I am Cantana and Resists.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Kalsyre Silverstring<br>
