</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udebbie112.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Debbie112</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/25/00 1:00:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: yea.. what Kal said..</span><hr size=1> Man, would you guys please pass this info on to other bards you see signed up for raids please?  I just left a failed Naggy raid with two other bards who insisted on being tanks while I stood back and twisted with the drum.  I'm sure others around not in my group wondered why I wasn't helping like the other bards as they have no clue the difference.  I won't name names, but some bards should just go make a tank if they don't want to do their duty.  Obviously these two bards playing tanks wasn't the only cause of a failed raid, but was for sure a contributing factor in why their tanks got wiped out so fast.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Deboria, 51st Minstrel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uatwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AtWork</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#CC9900>(9/25/00 7:48:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bard Question #1 - Dragons</span><hr size=1> I've only swung my weapon at Naggy once, and that was when the raid was failing but he was so close to dieing.  Did not help one bit.  Purely twist Elemental and Guardian only.  Tried for 3 once and the lag got too bad; so I stopped.  Whenever I go on a raid, I check to see who the other bards are.  If I don't know them, I try to have a little chat with them during the buffing circle time.  Got nothing else to do.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Needless to say, they got their drum out and sang away.<br>
<br>
The only weird thing that I have come across is being placed with the caster group.  Had this happen a couple of times.  The groups told me to keep the mana song up.  I asked then one question.  Do you want to cast or run in fear?<br>
<br>
Just talk to them before the fight and most will listen to an experienced raider.  Though I have coome across a few dense bards.  No names will be given, they will be shown the light.<br>
